# Samples and external content
Samples~/

# Generated perf artifacts: the raw NUnit XML, the auto-generated rolling
# baseline (perf-results/baseline.json), and the delta report
# (perf-results/perf-deltas.md / .json) are machine-written by the Unity
# Benchmarks workflow (scripts/unity/lib/render-perf-deltas.js). They are
# emitted prettier-shaped already, but keep the whole tree out of prettier's
# scope so a generated file can never trip `run-prettier.js --check` in CI.
perf-results/**

# Generated, deterministic skills index (scripts/generate-skills-index.ps1). Keep it
# out of Prettier so a formatting pass can never reshape the canonical bytes the
# linter enforces (UTF-8 no BOM, LF, ordinal order, unpadded table cells).
.llm/skills/index.md

# Only format supported text/assets; Prettier globbing will still be constrained by scripts
**/*.meta
**/*.unity
**/*.prefab
**/*.mat
**/*.asset

